news.title: Over 59 families in Kadakampally to receive land titles: Kerala revenue minister
news.para: This misclassification led to confusion, with many assuming the land to be a protected forest area. A detailed examination confirmed the land was ‘forest puramboke'—a non-forest govt land category.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body demolishes around 30 illegal structures on parking spaces
news.para: Despite repeated action by civic authorities, the issue remains unresolved. On Tuesday, the BBMP demolished around 30 temporary structures that had been set up illegally in the space meant for parking.

news.title: Prime minister set to relaunch Amaravati construction works on May 2
news.para: A total of 8,603 sq km was notified as the capital region, with 217 sq km allocated for the capital city and 16.9 sq km designated as the core capital area.

news.title: Construction debris, encroachments won't be tolerated during Delhi's cleanliness drive: Environment minister
news.para: According to Sirsa, the top leadership gave "firm, clear, and uncompromising directions" that no more construction debris (malba), garbage dumping or encroachments would be tolerated.

news.title: Net mortgage lending in UK surge by $17.27 billion in March 2025
news.para: Net mortgage borrowing rose by 12.963 billion pounds ($17.27 billion), the biggest jump since June 2021 during the COVID-19 pandemic which prompted a surge in the property market.

news.title: Resale home prices in China fall  0.7% in April 2025
news.para: "Price cuts to drive sales remained the market norm," the China Index Academy wrote in the report published on its official WeChat social media account on Thursday.

news.title: Europe's real estate recovery stalls amid global uncertainty in US president's second term: MSCI data
news.para: Property sales in Europe totalled 41 billion euros ($47 billion) in the first quarter of this year, down 11% on the previous year and breaking a run of three consecutive quarters of annual increases, the data showed.

news.title: Property registrations in Mumbai rises 8% to 52,896 units in Jan-Apr 2025: Anarock
news.para: In terms of registration numbers, 52,896 properties were registered in Mumbai in the first four months of 2025, as against 48,819 in the same period last year.

news.title: Kimco Realty revenue from rental properties rise 6.5% to $531.3 million in Q1 2025
news.para: The company expects its full-year funds from operations - a key REIT metric - to be between $1.71 and $1.74 per share, compared with a prior target of $1.70 to $1.72.

news.title: alt.f to invest ₹30 crore to open three new centres by 2025-end
news.para: alt.f recently opened 56,000 sq ft centre in Nanakramguda Financial District, Hyderabad with an investment of ₹8 crore. This is its first centre in the city and has over 1,200 seats capacity.

news.title: Pending home sales in US jumped 6.1% in March 2025
news.para: The National Association of Realtors (NAR) said on Wednesday its Pending Home Sales Index, based on signed contracts, jumped 6.1% to 76.5 last month. The increase was the largest since December 2023.

news.title: Home prices in Australia rise 0.3% in April 2025
news.para: Prices rose 0.3% in April from March to a new peak of A$ 825,349 ($528,470.96), compared with a 0.4% gain the previous month, figures from Cotality, formerly CoreLogic, showed.

news.title: Panchshil Realty to invest Rs 1,000 crore to develop IT Park in Indore
news.para: The Pune headquartered realty firm has delivered more than 32 million sq ft of IT Park in Pune which has generated more than 6 lakh jobs.

news.title: Telangana HC restrains GHMC, revenue officials from interfering with Banjara Hills property
news.para: The direction was given while hearing a writ petition filed by Buddi Prakash Toshniwal and others, who claimed ownership of the 600 square yard property.

news.title: Chennai: GCC mandates builders to curb construction dust or face penalty
news.para: At least 6,150 metric tonnes of solid waste is generated daily in the city. Additionally, about 800 metric tonnes of construction and demolition (C&D) waste are generated every day.

news.title: Builder dupes over 32 tenants in Bengaluru by leasing already sold flats
news.para: In January 2024, a man named Sai Prashant visited Padma and claimed ownership of the same flats, presenting registered sale deeds dated September 13, 2021.

news.title: Schindler posts 2.5% rise in revenue in Q1 2025
news.para: The Americas account for 29% of Schindler's group revenue, with over 95% of the raw materials and components the company uses in products sold in the U.S. sourced locally, analysts at Jefferies said.

news.title: Vulcan Materials' revenues rises 5.8% to $1.64 billion in Q1 2025
news.para: These supplies are part of Vulcan's construction aggregates business, its largest. The segment's gross profit rose 18% in the quarter, while margins expanded 320 basis points to 26.7%.
